deck: Jon Miller is one of the original founders of Outpouring Comics and the current CEO.  He currently is having a blast touring to promote the company and lines while writing for a number of lines that occur in the Outpouring Universe.
description: Jon Miller is one of the founders of Outpouring Comics and the current CEO. Jon started the Outpouring Universe in role plays and eventually decided with the rest of the founders of Outpouring Comics to bring those stories to comics and the written word. He wrote the initial run of VODA,Chronicles of Roshomon: Second Great War of Mysterium, Briggs Empire, and oversees the creation of all Outpouring Universe titles.
name: Jon Miller

deck: Kent Willis is the first artist that Outpouring Comics contracted for work.  He worked on Outpouring Comics' VODA issues 1-3 and has also lent his talents to Outpouring Comics' upcoming sword and sorcery novel CoR:SGWoM.
description:
Kent first started work with Outpouring Comics on their VODA series producing the art for issues 1-3 and has been with Outpouring on various projects ever since. He has contributed art to the first Outpouring Universe novel Chronicles of Roshomon.

Kent has been greatly influenced by Eastern art and puts a Western spin on it for a unique style he calls Urban Manga.
name: Kent Willis

deck: Sam Gardone is one of the original founders of Outpouring Comics.  Sam originally was working on the start-up comic book company Archangel Entertainment which merged into Jon's concept start-up that is now known as Outpouring Comics. He is an editor, writer, creator, and COO for Outpouring Comics.
name: Sam Gardone

deck: Neil Krolicki is a writer, illustrator and expert lover who writes darkly humorous fiction from a secret bunker somewhere Colorado. His stories have recently been showcased in Chuck Palahniuk's transgressive anthology, Burnt Tongues and ThugLit Issue 14. He's also the creative force behind 120 Doses, a crime-noir comic book about erasing the identities of ruthless criminals through radical reconstructive surgeries. Please visit www.120doses.com for more info.
